# Polinar i18n System

This project uses a dual i18n system:

## 1. CMS Content (Payload globals)
Managed via admin panel. Translations stored in DB, served via `payload.findGlobal({ slug, locale })`.

## 2. Static Content (src/data/ modules)
Hardcoded page content uses locale-aware data files:

```
src/data/{page-slug}/
  types.ts   — TypeScript type definition
  en.ts      — English content (source of truth)
  tr.ts      — Turkish translation
  index.ts   — Loader using createLocaleLoader with EN fallback
```

### Creating a new static page

1. Write `src/data/{slug}/en.ts` with all translatable strings
2. Run `npm run i18n:create-page {slug}` — auto-generates types.ts, index.ts, and all locale files
3. Import in component: `import { getSlugData } from '@/data/{slug}'`
4. Call `const data = getSlugData(locale)` — returns EN fallback if locale file is missing

### Shared labels

`getStaticLabels(locale)` from `@/data/static-labels` provides: company info, SEO defaults, breadcrumbs, aria-labels, product UI strings.

### Key files

- `src/data/locale-loader.ts` — createLocaleLoader utility
- `src/data/static-labels/` — shared translatable strings
- `src/lib/i18n-helpers.ts` — CMS import/export helpers
- `scripts/create-static-page.ts` — auto-generator for new pages
